<sect1 id="tool-ekos">
    <title>Ekos</title>
    <indexterm>
        <primary>Tools</primary>
        <secondary>Ekos</secondary>
    </indexterm>
    <para>
        <emphasis role="bold">Ekos</emphasis>
        is an advanced observatory control and automation tool with a particular focus on astrophotography.
    </para>
    <para>Use Ekos to control your telescope, camera, filter wheel, focuser, guider, adaptive optics unit, and any INDI-compatible auxiliary device.</para>
    <para>If you want to dive straight in, try the
        <link linkend="ekos-quick-start">Quick Start Guide</link>
        .
    </para>
    <para>
        <emphasis role="bold">Ekos</emphasis>
        is integrated with
        <ulink url="http://edu.kde.org/kstars">&kstars;</ulink>
        and both are pre-installed on INDI based devices and OS distributions like
        <ulink url="https://www.stellarmate.com/component/jdownloads/category/2-ekos.html?Itemid=507">StellarMate</ulink>
        and Astroberry. KStars and Ekos can be installed on &Linux;, &MacOS;, and &Windows; computers.
    </para>
    <para>Each module of Ekos is opened by clicking its icon on the Ekos Toolbar.</para>
    <screenshot>
        <screeninfo>Ekos Toolbar</screeninfo>
        <mediaobject>
            <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="ekos_module_toolbar.png" format="PNG"/>
